'''Tyrick Bodak''' (born 15 May 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Dutch football updater|Telstar}} club [[SC Telstar|Telstar]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|608777}}</ref>

== Club career ==
Bodak came through the youth system at [[De Graafschap]] and joined [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] in June 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=PSV plukt keeper Tyrick Bodak (17) weg bij De Graafschap |url=https://www.ed.nl/psv/psv-plukt-keeper-tyrick-bodak-17-weg-bij-de-graafschap~a5917675/ |work=Eindhovens Dagblad |language=nl |date=6 June 2019 |access-date=10 October 2021}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract on 11 August 2020.<ref name="pccuw">{{cite news |title=BAS trots op 1e profcontract bij PSV van oud-doelman Tyrick Bodak |url=https://www.omroepflevoland.nl/sport/188706/bas-trots-op-1e-profcontract-bij-psv-van-oud-doelman-tyrick-bodak |work=Omroep Flevoland |language=nl |date=12 August 2021 |access-date=10 October 2021}}</ref> In June 2023, he moved to [[SC Cambuur|Cambuur]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Boeringa |first1=Reon |title=SC Cambuur winkelt bij Jong PSV en heeft talent AZ op de radar |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/sc-cambuur-winkelt-bij-jong-psv-en-heeft-talent-az-op-de-radar |access-date=5 November 2025 |work=Voetbal International |date=7 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608023257/https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/sc-cambuur-winkelt-bij-jong-psv-en-heeft-talent-az-op-de-radar |archive-date=8 June 2023 |language=nl-NL |trans-title=SC Cambuur sign from Jong PSV and target AZ youngster}}</ref>

In 2024, Bodak joined [[SC Telstar|Telstar]] in the [[Eerste Divisie]], where he was the third-choice goalkeeper behind [[Ronald Koeman Jr.|Ronald Koeman jr.]] and [[Joey Houweling]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Twee spelers van Telstar opgeroepen voor nationaal elftal. Turfkruier en Bodak missen nu geen duel in Nederland |url=https://www.haarlemsdagblad.nl/sport/telstar/twee-spelers-van-telstar-opgeroepen-voor-nationaal-elftal.-turfkruier-en-bodak-missen-nu-geen-duel-in-nederland/48422041.html |work=Haarlems Dagblad |language=nl |date=11 March 2025 |url-access=subscription |access-date=5 November 2025 |trans-title=Two Telstar players called up for national team; Turfkruier and Bodak set to miss no matches in the Netherlands}}</ref> He was part of the squad that won promotion to the [[Eredivisie]] through the play-offs in the [[2024–25 SC Telstar season|2024–25 season]]—the club's first top-flight return in 47 years—albeit without making an appearance.<ref>{{cite news |title=Telstar keert na 47 jaar terug in de Eredivisie, Willem II degradeert |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/telstar-keert-na-47-jaar-terug-in-de-eredivisie-willem-ii-degradeert |work=Voetbal International |language=nl |date=1 June 2025 |access-date=2 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250601180432/https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/telstar-keert-na-47-jaar-terug-in-de-eredivisie-willem-ii-degradeert |archive-date=1 June 2025 |trans-title=Telstar return to the Eredivisie after 47 years, Willem II relegated}}</ref> Following promotion he remained third-choice, with [[Daan Reiziger]] arriving to back up Koeman jr.<ref>{{cite web |title=Telstar versterkt zich met Daan Reiziger |url=https://sctelstar.nl/nieuws/telstar-versterkt-zich-met-daan-reiziger |website=SC Telstar |language=nl |date=15 July 2025 |access-date=12 October 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251012145026/https://sctelstar.nl/nieuws/telstar-versterkt-zich-met-daan-reiziger |archive-date=12 October 2025 |trans-title=Telstar strengthen with Daan Reiziger}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Daan Reiziger uit Stad tekent voor twee jaar bij Telstar |url=https://www.rtvnoord.nl/sport/1323243/daan-reiziger-uit-stad-tekent-voor-twee-jaar-bij-telstar |work=RTV Noord |language=nl |date=14 July 2025 |access-date=30 September 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250930204339/https://www.rtvnoord.nl/sport/1323243/daan-reiziger-uit-stad-tekent-voor-twee-jaar-bij-telstar |archive-date=30 September 2025 |trans-title=Daan Reiziger from Groningen signs two-year deal with Telstar}}</ref>

==International career==
Bodak has represented Curaçao at youth level.<ref name=pccuw/> In July 2021, he was named in [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao's]] squad for the [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gold Cup 2021 Team Profile Curaçao|url=http://www.insideworldfootball.com/2021/07/02/gold-cup-2021-team-profile-curacao/|date=2 July 2021|access-date=10 October 2021}}</ref> However, they were forced to withdraw from the tournament due to high number of [[COVID-19]] positive cases across the staff and players.<ref>{{cite web|title=Concacaf Statement – Curacao Delegation at 2021 Gold Cup|url=https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/concacaf-statement-curacao-delegation-at-2021-gold-cup/|date=9 July 2021|access-date=11 June 2025}}</ref>

Bodak made his international debut on 9 October 2021 in a 2–1 defeat to [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kiwi's verpesten Curaçao-debuut jonge PSV-doelman|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/kiwis-verpesten-curacao-debuut-jonge-psv-doelman|date=9 October 2021|access-date=10 October 2021}}</ref> In June 2025, he was named in the squad for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rosters confirmed for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/gold-cup/news/rosters-confirmed-for-2025-concacaf-gold-cup/|date=5 June 2025|access-date=11 June 2025}}</ref> In May 2026, he was named in Curaçao's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], the country's first-ever appearance at the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Smallest nation Curacao name debut World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c70798249j0o|date=18 May 2026|access-date=18 May 2026}}</ref>

